                            <comment id="65270" author="dyret" created="Fri, 13 May 2005 19:09:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This happens because the ANT-task that runs the splitmessages.java program supplies the two arguments (a directory and a property file) with a &amp;lt;arg line=&quot;...&quot;/&amp;gt; element. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ANT manual (&lt;a href=&quot;http://ant.apache.org/manual/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://ant.apache.org/manual/&lt;/a&gt;), says &quot;Ant will try to split the command line in a way similar to what a (Unix) shell would do, but may create something that is very different from what you expect under some circumstances.&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
And that is what happens. With spaces in the file names the shell-like splitting will cause splitmessages.java to be started with more than two arguments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The solution is to replace the &amp;lt;arg line=&quot;...&quot;/&amp;gt; element in java/engine/org/apache/derby/loc/build.xml&lt;br/&gt;
with a pair of &amp;lt;arg value=&quot;...&quot;/&amp;gt; elements. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
